<!-- ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
Rule: boundary_size_characteristic_constraint
++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ -->
<ext_description linkend="Extended_geometric_tolerance_mim.boundary_size_characteristic_constraint">
The <b>boundary_size_characteristic_constraint</b> rule constrains the use of a representation when it is used as a boundary size characteristic.
</ext_description>

<ext_description linkend="Extended_geometric_tolerance_mim.boundary_size_characteristic_constraint.wr:WR1">
<p>Each representation with a name of either 'diametrical boundary size' or 'opposing boundary set size' shall contain exactly one <express_ref linkend="measure_schema:ir_express:measure_schema.length_measure_with_unit"/> that has a name of 'tolerance value'.
</p></ext_description>

